        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-05-06T15:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-05-06T15:30:00-05:00" n="97"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                <head>97. Notes of Telephone Conversation Between the President’s Assistant for
                    National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_KHA1" type="from"
                        >Kissinger</persName>) and Secretary of Defense <persName corresp="#p_LMR2"
                        type="to">Laird</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d97fn1">Source: Library of Congress,
                        Manuscript Division, <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>
                        Papers, Box 359, Telephone Conversations, Chronological File, 1–14 May 1969.
                        No classification marking.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d97fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_LMR2">Laird</persName> discussed the next steps in the
                        “Seabed matter.”</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1969-05-06T16:30:00-04:00">May 6, 1969, 4:30 p.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion unrelated to seabeds.]</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss> said he would do it, but they are concerned
                    about <gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss>’s Seabed thing. <gloss target="#t_K1"
                        >K</gloss> said not to worry about it. <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said
                    he called Dave on Seabed matter and if <gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss> could get
                    him some of his suggested changes he would appreciate it. <gloss target="#t_L1"
                        >L</gloss> said they were sent over a couple of days ago. <gloss
                        target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said President then said he would talk to Gerry and
                    say his condition for going ahead with it would be to include <gloss
                        target="#t_L1">L</gloss>’s changes - that way he could buy more time on
                        <gloss target="#t_SALT1">SALT</gloss>. <gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss> said
                    he understood. <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said Pres will not make a ruling
                    like that until everyone has chance to express views.</p>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion unrelated to seabeds.]</p>
            </div>
